Package org.opensextant.geodesy

Class ISO8601DateTimePoint

java.lang.Object
org.opensextant.geodesy.ISO8601DateTimePoint
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<ISO8601DateTimePoint>
Direct Known Subclasses:
ISO8601DateTimeInterval
public class ISO8601DateTimePoint extends Object implements Comparable<ISO8601DateTimePoint>
The ISO8601DateTimePoint class is a simple wrapper for a time instant standardized as a number of milliseconds since midnight Jan 1, 1970 GMT. This class has a String constructor and toString method that respectively parse and format dates and times in the ISO 8601 format. Partial dates are parsed to the beginning of the time interval they define.
